'''[[同盟國軍事佔領德國|同盟國佔領德國]]期間的強姦'''，指二戰結束後盟軍對德國女性的[[強姦|強姦]]，包括蘇軍、美軍、英軍和法軍。長期以來此事在國際媒體上鮮受關注。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/3255081/German-women-break-their-silence-on-horrors-of-Red-Army-rapes.html|title=German women break their silence on horrors of Red Army rapes|author=Allan Hall in Berlin|date=24 October 2008|work=Telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=10 December 2014|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128110117/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/germany/3255081/German-women-break-their-silence-on-horrors-of-Red-Army-rapes.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="The Independent">{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/raped-by-the-red-army-two-million-german-women-speak-out-1669074.html|title=Raped by the Red Army: Two million German women speak out|work=The Independent|accessdate=10 December 2014|archive-date=2020-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117032901/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/raped-by-the-red-army-two-million-german-women-speak-out-1669074.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Susanne Beyer">{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,680354,00.html|title=Harrowing Memoir: German Woman Writes Ground-Breaking Account of WW2 Rape|author=Susanne Beyer|publisher=Spiegel.de|accessdate=10 December 2014|archive-date=2010-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100301052729/http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,680354,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==蘇聯==
强奸主要發生在[[德国苏占区|德国苏占区]]。約2,000,000婦女被[[蘇聯紅軍|蘇聯紅軍]]强奸<ref name="ElizabethHeineman">{{cite journal |first=Elizabeth |last=Heineman |title=The Hour of the Woman: Memories of Germany's "Crisis Years" and West German National Identity |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-historical-review_1996-04_101_2/page/354 |journal=[[American_Historical_Review|American Historical Review]] |volume=101 |issue=2 |year=1996 |pages=354–395 |jstor=2170395 |doi=10.2307/2170395 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kuwert |first1=P. |last2=Freyberger |first2=H. |year=2007 |title=The unspoken secret: Sexual violence in World War II |journal=International Psychogeriatrics |volume=19 |issue=4 |pages=782–784 |doi=10.1017/S1041610207005376 |pmid=17726764 }}</ref><ref name="BBC">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/history/worldwars/wwtwo/berlin_01.shtml|title=BBC - History - World Wars: The Battle for Berlin in World War Two|publisher=Bbc.co.uk|accessdate=10 December 2014|archive-date=2020-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204140748/http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/worldwars/wwtwo/berlin_01.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Schissler2001">{{cite book|last=Heineman|first=Elizabeth|editor=Hanna Schissler|title=The Miracle Years: A Cultural History of West Germany, 1949–1968|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=00fCzJKt1QMC&pg=PA28|accessdate=27 January 2018|year=2001|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=0-691-05820-2|page=28|chapter=The Hour of the Woman: Memories of Germany's 'Crisis Years' and West German National Identity|archive-date=2020-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200830142239/https://books.google.com/books?id=00fCzJKt1QMC&pg=PA28|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。根據史學家William Hitchcock的著述，很多婦女被輪奸，有些多達六七十次<ref name="Struggle for Europe">{{cite book |first=William I. |last=Hitchcock |title=The Struggle for Europe: The Turbulent History of a Divided Continent, 1945 to the Present |publisher=Anchor Books |year=2004 |url=http://www.randomhouse.com/catalog/display.pperl?isbn=9780385497992&view=excerpt |isbn=978-0-385-49799-2 |access-date=2020-11-19 |archive-date=2019-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404155035/http://www.randomhouse.com/catalog/display.pperl?isbn=9780385497992&view=excerpt |dead-url=no }}</ref>。至少100,000名婦女在[[柏林|柏林]]被强奸<ref name="BBC"/>，約10,000名婦女在之後死亡<ref name="Grossman">Atina Grossmann. A Question of Silence: The Rape of German Women by Occupation Soldiers ''October'', Vol. 72, ''Berlin 1945: War and Rape "Liberators Take Liberties"'' (Spring, 1995), pp. 42–63 MIT Press</ref>。

==美國==
J. Robert Lilly 估計11,040名婦女被美軍强奸<ref>Taken by Force: Rape and American GIs in Europe during World War II. J Robert Lilly. {{ISBN|978-0-230-50647-3}} p.12</ref>。[[D日|D日]]美軍攻下法國後，繼續進攻德國，很多德國婦女在1945年被美軍強奸<ref name = "Harrington 2010, 80-81">Harrington, Carol (2010). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=SjspAcONy-gC Politicization of Sexual Violence: From Abolitionism to Peacekeeping.] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SjspAcONy-gC |date=20210225184524 }}'' London: Ashgate. pp. 80–81. {{ISBN|0-7546-7458-4}}.</ref>。

==英國==
按Sean Longden著述，英軍有[[憲兵隊|憲兵隊]]審查軍紀，定期處理强奸報告，强奸規模遠小於蘇聯紅軍，但依舊零星發生强奸案件<ref  name="sfn">{{cite book | ref=harv |last=Longden |first=Sean|title=To the Victor the Spoils|date=25 July 2013|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=978-1-4721-1218-7 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=2CmeBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT153 140]–141}}</ref>。

他的著述提及1945年4月16日[[呂本山麓諾伊施塔特|呂本山麓諾伊施塔特]]有3名婦女被英軍强奸<ref  name="sfn"/>。

==法國== 
Perry Biddiscombe援引原始檔案估計法軍在[[康斯坦茨|康斯坦茨]]作了385起强奸案，在[[布魯赫薩爾|布魯赫薩爾]]約600起，在[[弗羅伊登施塔特|弗羅伊登施塔特]]約500起<ref>{{cite journal |first=Perry |last=Biddiscombe |title=Dangerous Liaisons: The Anti-Fraternization Movement in the U.S. Occupation Zones of Germany and Austria, 1945–1948 |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-social-history_spring-2001_34_3/page/635 |journal=Journal of Social History |volume=34 |issue=3 |year=2001 |pages=635 |jstor=3789820 |doi=10.1353/jsh.2001.0002 }}</ref> 。三地總共約1,485起强奸。其他地區也有强奸傳聞，但數據不明。

